Here are the MSTest attributes/patterns for each scenario:

**1. Windows-only (platform filter):**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)] // or use a manual check:
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.Windows))
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows");
    // ...
}
```

**2. Skip in CI (conditional skip):**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuTest()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU");
    // ...
}
```
Then filter in CI: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

**3. Flaky external API (retry):**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // MSTest 3.x+ — retries up to 3 times on failure
public void WeatherApiTest()
{
    var result = CallWeatherApi();
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```
> `[Retry]` was added in **MSTest v3.8**. On older versions, use `[DataRow]` with a manual retry loop or a custom attribute.

**4. Cleanup even on failure — use `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally`:**
```csharp
private string? _tempFile;

[TestInitialize]
public void Setup() => _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();

[TestCleanup] // runs even if the test fails
public void Cleanup()
{
    if (_tempFile != null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
        File.Delete(_tempFile);
}

[TestMethod]
public void TempFileTest()
{
    File.WriteAllText(_tempFile!, "data");
    Assert.IsTrue(File.Exists(_tempFile));
}
```

**Key takeaways:**
| Scenario | Mechanism |
|---|---|
| Platform gate | `Assert.Inconclusive()` or condition attribute |
| CI skip | `[TestCategory]` + filter, or env-var check |
| Flaky retry | `[Retry(N)]` (MSTest 3.8+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` (always runs post-test) |
